com.tymeac.base

Class RequestDetail

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tymeac.base.RequestDetail

  • public final class RequestDetail
extends java.lang.Object
    A request detail object. Contains fields necessary to track the request. There is a basic part that is common to both async and sync. There are two additional parts for async and for sync.

      • setComp

        protected void setComp(int code)
        Set the completion code. It may look like a race condition but only one thread will update this field and only when there is a problem. If two threads have a problem at the same time, so what. Only one status can go back so it really doesn't matter.
        Parameters:
        code - int - completion code from queue thread

      • setDecrement

        protected int setDecrement(AreaBase que)
        Decrement number of queues remaining to be processed and null the queue in the array of queue names that did the processing.
        Returns:
        int

      • setFree

        protected void setFree()
        Remove the entry from the details list and mark as freed

      • setLatchZero

        private void setLatchZero()
        Set the latch count to zero since we don't interrupt the waiting thread

      • setOutput

        protected void setOutput(java.lang.Object obj)
        Set the output object into the output object array
        Parameters:
        obj - Object

      • setPosted

        private void setPosted()
        Set the awaiting (maybe) request as finished. The request may not have reached the await yet. Doing a countDown() when no thread is waiting has no affect.

      • setQueNull

        private void setQueNull(AreaBase que)
        Null the second queue reference in the array of queue names. We need a duelie since we cannot null a reference that another thread may pick up at any time. It may look like a race condition but each thread only modifies one element in the list.
        Parameters:
        que - AreaBase

      • setReset

        private boolean setReset()
        Set the status code to 'reset' (the monitor will flush this request when next it runs)
